{"data":{"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"b745f057-82e4-5177-bb94-fae519f66ae9","excerpt":"Interactions in games are fascinating because usually people have a gut feeling of when the game feels right, but it’s not an easy task to replicate the experience. Controls and how the character follows players interactions are vital in platform…","frontmatter":{"date":"June 30, 2019","path":"/writings/ux-of-a-platform-game","title":"Platformer (game) UX","tags":["hci"],"summary":"Some years ago I tried building a platformer game (PC / Android) and found the experience interesting from the UX point of view. This is my recap of what I remember. TLDR: You can cheat to make it feel more like a game. Physics simulation rarely makes a good game (at least you'll need to fine tune your character movement physics).","featuredImage":{"id":"57986dfe-0ee0-5004-b6bc-724c88fc09db","childImageSharp":{"id":"78c2497b-eace-5dd2-8e44-c79145c53790","sizes":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.3333333333333333,"src":"/static/59c5630f6238d78b19272827bb560611/e1953/Corner-cases-in-platformer-physics.003.png","srcSet":"/static/59c5630f6238d78b19272827bb560611/72176/Corner-cases-in-platformer-physics.003.png 63w,\n/static/59c5630f6238d78b19272827bb560611/62d80/Corner-cases-in-platformer-physics.003.png 125w,\n/static/59c5630f6238d78b19272827bb560611/e1953/Corner-cases-in-platformer-physics.003.png 250w,\n/static/59c5630f6238d78b19272827bb560611/c6fa8/Corner-cases-in-platformer-physics.003.png 375w,\n/static/59c5630f6238d78b19272827bb560611/46604/Corner-cases-in-platformer-physics.003.png 500w,\n/static/59c5630f6238d78b19272827bb560611/a8378/Corner-cases-in-platformer-physics.003.png 1024w","sizes":"(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px"}}}}}},{"node":{"id":"0d352139-8c7a-5e45-9b65-42b8ce628ce2","excerpt":"Automation and analytics are good means to improve operator and overall system performance. Ever increasing amount of data means that in many situations human operators are no l